Program: Free Thinking
Title: New Research into the UK Women's Suffrage Movement
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b09th2dt
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 8 Mar 2018
How did interior design help gain women the vote? Were arson attacks justified? Who took part in a six-week march? What role did an Indian princess play? Helen Pankhurst, Jane Robinson, Fern Ridell, Shahida Rahman and Miranda Garrett discuss the history of women's suffrage with Eleanor Rosamund Barraclough in this centenary year of the Bill which gave some women the right to vote. Fern Riddell is the author of Death in 10 Minutes - Kitty Marion: Activist, Arsonist, Suffragette Helen Pankhurst is the author of Deeds Not Words: The Story of Women's Rights, Then and Now. Jane Robinson has written Hearts and Minds: The Untold Story of the Great Pilgrimage and How Women Won the Vote. Miranda Garrett is co editor with ZoÃ« Thomas of Suffrage and the Arts: Visual Culture, Politics and Enterprise Producer: Fiona McLean. Show less